      • isConstraintSupportedAfterNullability

        public boolean isConstraintSupportedAfterNullability()
        Gets whether the database platform supports adding contraints after the NULL constraint. Some database, such as Oracle, don't allow this. Unfortunately, EclipsLink hard codes the order of constraints.
        Specified by:
        isConstraintSupportedAfterNullability in interface DbmsHelper
        Returns:
        true if contraints can be added after the NULL constraint, false otherwise.
